Abstract: The determinants of the outcomes of business negotiations in 3 cultures are investigated in a laboratory experiment. The outcomes of negotiations between Japanese businessmen result primarily from situational constraint&mdash;the role of the negotiator (buyer or seller). Representational (problem-solving oriented) bargaining strategies, a measure of the process of the interaction, is the most important variable in American negotiations. In negotiations between Brazilian business people, deceptive bargaining strategies&mdash;also a process measure&mdash;is the key variable affecting outcomes.&copy; 1983 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1983) 14, 47&ndash;61
